Rating: 4
This is an awesome recipe. One of the most amazing things is that it uses no flour, and no flour is required. I did not use lemon peel. I used 70% Schaffer Berger chocolate for the chocolate, and the taste of the torte is exceptional. Nick Malgeri makes the same torte using walnuts, and just a touch of flour. Next time, I might add a touch of flour. Without the flour, this is a perfect desert recipe for Passover, and Schaffer Berger chocolate (top rated with Santender by Gourmet Magazine) is kosher.

